* FIRST CLASS MENU
Westbound and Seattle and Portland to Los Angeles
Food and drinks are served right after takeoff, but if you'd like to be served later,
no problem. Just ask your in-flight team.
BREAKFAST
Flights departing before 10am
EGG AND VEGETABLE PIE
WITH WINTER FRUIT SALAD
Scrambled eggs with light cream cheese, chives, roasted
crimini mushrooms, Brussels sprouts, and a root vegetable
mix of carrot, turnip, parsnip, golden beet, sweet potato,
onion, and thyme. On the side are chicken-apple sausages,
a togarashi-seasoned puff, and a fresh fruit salad of
pineapple, blueberries, strawberries, and Amarena cherries.
olildis Udily ano wheat
FRUIT PLATE WITH GRANOLA
A selection of fresh pineapple, grapefruit, orange, green
grapes, kiwi, mango, and strawberries served with Udi's
granola, milk, low-fat vanilla yogurt, and a blueberry garnish.
Contains nuts and dairy.
MID-FLIGHT SNACK
Westbound flights over four hours
PITA ROUNDS WITH RATATOUILLE TAPENADE
Roasted tomato and olive chickpea tapenade,
with whole wheat pita slices, dolma, and cucumber,
and a decadent chocolate truffle dessert.
Contains wheat and dairy.
LUNCH & DINNER
Flights departing after 10am
APPETIZER
Westbound flights over four hours
ROASTED PEAR SALAD WITH GOAT CHEESE
Roasted pear and gratin of goat cheese, served on
arugula mesclun salad, with toasted walnuts, dried figs,
grape tomato, and fig vinaigrette.
Contains dairy and nuts.
ENTRÉES
FILET OF BEEF SALTIMBOCCA
Prosciutto-wrapped beef filet, served with sautéed
mushrooms, horseradish-chive mashed potatoes, onions,
and green and yellow beans.
Contains beef, pork and dairy.
PUMPKIN RAVIOLI
WITH BROWN BUTTER AND SAGE
Pumpkin and sage-stuffed al dente ravioli, with roasted
butternut squash, toasted hazelnuts, roasted tomato,
and sage brown butter sauce - all garnished with fresh
sage leaves and parsley.
Contains wheat, dairy and nuts.
DESSERT
CHOCOLATE COCONUT BAR
By Sweet Lady Jane
Contains dairy, wheat and sugar
DRINKS
Please ask the in-flight team for today's wine selections.
RED WINE
Circadia Cabernet Sauvignon, 2010
A delightful array of tropical fruit flavors ripping through the rich
and silky palate. Subtle hints of French Oak spice gracefully
weave their way to a finish displaying enviable length.
WHITE WINE
Circadia Chardonnay, 2011
Al diluring wine with seductive dark truit flavors, medium Dody
and exquisite, soft texture. This is a wine of great intensity
with a timeless sense of elegance.
THE GOOD STUFF
La Grand Courtâge Sparkling Wine
360 Vodka
Bacardi Rum
Bombay Sapphire Gin
Veev Açai Spirit
Jack Daniel's
Glenfiddich Single Malt Scotch Whisky
Tequila Cazadores Reposado
Baileys Irish Cream
Anchor Steam Beer
Samuel Adams Lager
Bud Light
21st Amendment Back in Black
Heineken
THE GOOD STUFF
(MINUS THE BOOZE)
ROCKSTAR Recovery
EBOOST
Honest Ade - Pomegranate Blue
Honest Tea - Honey Green
Mighty Leaf Classic Breakfast Tea
Mighty Leaf Chamomile Citrus
Mighty Leaf Organic Spring Jasmine
Bottled Water
Philz Tesora Blend Coffee
Decaffeinated Coffee
Coca-Cola
Coke Zero
Diet Coke
Ginger Ale
Sprite
Sprite Zero
Seltzer
Tonic Water
Orange Juice
Apple Juice
Cranberry-Apple Juice
Tomato Juice
Bloody Mary Mix
*Our apologies if your first choice is unavailable.
Rest assured, your second choice will be just as delicious.
2018.088.017
